The Mechanic
"A Screenplay inspired by The Car"
 
 
written by
 
 
Maha E.S.
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
WORDS are typed on the bottom of the BLACK screen in courier typeface to the SOUND of a typewriter keys CLICKING:
WASHINGTON. JUNE 17, 1972
MORE words are typed:
...JUST AFTER MIDNIGHT
We hear anxious PANTING in the dark.
The SOUND of a light switch being activated ECHOES in the empty lot.
fade in:
int. AirCRAFT Hangar - NIGHT
One single light beam ILLUMINATES down over a seated MAN. His eyes squinting adjusting to the brightness.
WORDS are typed on the bottom of the screen in courier typeface to the SOUND of a typewriter keys CLICKING:
THE MECHANIC
 
A boyishly handsome but hard-worn English man, in his 30's, wearing a mechanic-style GREEN JACKET over a shirt and jeans. He has cuts, bruises, and dry blood on his face.
His wrists are CUFFED to the leg of the steel TABLE in front of him. An empty chair faces him on the other side with a CAMERA set on a tall tripod behind it.
A RED light FLICKERS in the top corner of the camera screen. He is being watched and recorded.
The hangar doors OPEN and loudly SHUT. Sounds of unified STEPS steadily approaching. Two AGENTS in matching black suits, make their way towards him. The parallel neon LIGHTS above them ACTIVATE, one by one as they move in closer.
A third AGENT with thinning hair in a more casual suit, no tie, carrying a leather BRIEFCASE approaches behind them.
AGENT
Sorry to keep you waiting.
He sits in the chair SIGNALING for the seated man to be uncuffed. The Mechanic rubs his freed wrists.
2.
His thumb sliding over the SYMBOL tattooed on his skin. An image of TWO OVERLAPPING LOOPS.
The agent offers him a CIGARETTE. The Mechanic turns to the guards on either side of him.
MECHANIC
(looking at the agent)
The good cop, bad cop routine?
A PUNCH is delivered to his face from the guard to his left. The Mechanic is hunched groaning.
AGENT
Im agent Baldwin.
WORDS are typed on the bottom of the screen in courier typeface to the SOUND of a typewriter keys CLICKING:
AGENT BALDWIN
A hard faced, no non-sense type with a self-assured presence to him.
From the BRIEFCASE he pulls a FOLDER running his fingers across the CONFIDENTIAL stamp on the front.
BALDWIN
You know...Ive been following your every move for a year now...from France to Mexico.
Sliding a series of black and white laminated PHOTOS on the table towards the Mechanic.
Baldwin
Don't you two look cozy.
It's a surveillance PHOTO of the Mechanic embracing a WOMAN. Her face is hidden.
BALDWIN
For a while, I thought you two were just a copycat...another Bonnie and Clyde type. Or whatever rouge cheap knockoffs you Brits have...Maybe James Bond and...Moneypenny?(smiles mockingly)...Nah! Moneypenny would never sell out Bond.
Baldwin slides another PHOTO across the table.
3.
BALDWIN
And she certainly wouldnt run off with him now...would she?
The Mechanic doesn't break eye contact with Baldwin. We don't see the PHOTO he pulled across to get that reaction.
BALDWIN
Why do they call you Mechanic? Hmm?
No answer.
BALDWIN
The recordings...(he waits)...what about the Faberg egg? Or did they run off with that too?
Pausing before he speaks.
MECHANIC
(looking around)
Why am I here? It's a little elaborate for an interrogation room.
Baldwin smirks.
MECHANIC
The camera, your guard dogs, and...
He looks over his shoulder. We see a CLOSED door. To his right a wall with a window sized VENTILATION slot.
MECHANIC
...no two way mirror. I hear crickets and I smell grass. We're in the middle of nowhere.
BALDWIN
Is that so?
MECHANIC
You said you were in France watching us...so what are you? Interpol?...FBI?...I don't think you even showed me a badge. Don't I get a phone call or something?
BALDWIN
Anyone ever tell you, you talk too much?...Maybe that's why you're here.
Baldwin pauses.
4.
BALDWIN
(leaning in)
I'll be asking the questions.
Baldwin's face hardens noting the arrogance of the man sitting across from him.
BALDWIN
And as far as who I am...I'm the only reason you're still breathing right now without a tube shoved down your throat. But I can easily turn that around. Good enough an answer for you?
Not responding, the Mechanic maintains eye contact.
BALDWIN
Good...now heres where we stand...Fortuna and Schwartz are off the grid and youre gonna tell us where they are...
Pointing towards the pack of CIGARETTES and empty coffee CUP on the table, the Mechanic reaches for them. Baldwin leans in, LIGHTING the Mechanic's CIGARETTE.
BALDWIN
Why dont you start from the beginning.
There is a short pause before he speaks. He takes a drag.
MECHANIC
I can still see the island...(exhales smoke)
I AINT QUITE WHERE I THINK I AM STARTS PLAYING.
cut TO:
EXT. LUXURY CRUISE LINER - FRENCH RIVIERA - DAY
A SERIES OF SHOTS: the ocean, picturesque villages on the hillside, aerial views of private luxury estates, crowds enjoying the pool, drinking, dancing to the music.
 
 
 
5.
Cut to:
INT. Cruise Liner CASINO - DAY
A SERIES OF SHOTS: a casino atmosphere, chatter, crowded poker and blackjack tables. A WAITRESS dressed in a sequin dress is making her way to the back bar. She moves past the Mechanic. He is seated hunched over drinking alone. A brown leather jacket polishing his all black ensemble.
He looks a little drunk.
The BARTENDER behind the counter moves closer WIPING the countertop. He slides over a KEY on the bar under his dish towel.
BARTENDER
(not looking up)
Robin left the nest...
Behind the Mechanic, A BELGIAN JEWELLER sits down at a blackjack table flirtatiously eyeing two tanned MEN.
BARTENDER
Are you sure you can do this?
Brushing him off, the Mechanic finishes his DRINK and takes the KEY.
MECHANIC
Meet me in 10 minutes...
Clearly a little drunk, he makes his way through the crowded room towards the MAIN HALL outside the casino.
INT. STAIRWELL: MAIN HALL - DAY
The Mechanic walks up a spiraling STAIRCASE towards the LUXURY SUITES.
CUT TO:
"I AINT QUITE WHERE I THINK I AM" abruptly STOPS on a note that ECHOES.
He pauses in the HALLWAY making sure he isn't followed.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
It was supposed to be an easy job.
He moves quietly down the HALLWAY.
6.
MECHANIC (V.O. CONTD)
The target was this...up-and-coming jeweller, they called him The Hand. It was supposed to be a quick grab. He travelled light with minimum security, no entourage. It was two of us. Just crack the safe, grab the jewels, and then...rendezvous with The English back in the city.
BACK TO:
BALDWIN
Mark...
He drops the surveillance PHOTO on the table.
BALDWIN
AKA, The English. We got him two weeks ago. Nevada. Hes been running operations from his hotel.
Pausing.
BALDWIN
Hes a bit of a nut job, your boss. We can't question him until we get a psych evaluation...and what happened to the jewels?
MECHANIC
The necklace...it was a decoy.
CUT TO:
The Mechanic is standing outside the ROOM numbered 505 holding the KEY.
INT. SUITE 505 - DAY
He scans the hotel ROOM amused at the lack of security measures.
Moving into the WALK IN CLOSET, he finds the SAFE. Confusion crowds his already intoxicated expression.
Its OPEN.
SOMEONE ELSE (O.S.)
Looking for this?
7.
STARTLED, he turns facing a WOMAN. WORDS are typed on the bottom of the screen in courier typeface to the SOUND of a typewriter keys CLICKING:
"FORTUNA
A stunning red-haired American woman in her late 20's. The kind of beauty that makes you look twice. An icy like magnetism to her. She is dressed in a black cocktail dress pointing a gun at him.
She holds the NECKLACE.
FORTUNA
Really?
She pauses looking him over.
FORTUNA
Are you...drinking on the job?
MECHANIC
(confused)
How do you- wait...Mark sent you?
FORTUNA
(cocks her gun)
No...but now I know youre not alone.
MECHANIC
Woah whoa! Wait!
She doesnt back down.
MECHANIC
I'm not armed I swear. Im just the cranes and wires guy.
FORTUNA
(irritated)
Cranes and...what?
MECHANIC
I...I can break into anything. They just let me do all the handy work. And numbers.
BACK to:
BALDWIN
Numbers?
8.
MECHANIC
Cracking codes, patterns.
CUT to:
MECHANIC
I swear I know nothing.
FORTUNA
Well, I dont doubt that...
She thinks it over.
FORTUNA
You can break into anything?
MECHANIC
Yea...Yes! Thats all. I know nothing. Ask Trevor! He'll tell you. We're working together.
They turn to see the bartender, TREVOR, standing by the door.
TREVOR
...you sloppy drunk.
Trevor AIMS his GUN at the Mechanic. Fortuna AIMS hers at Trevor. Unlike Trevor, she's completely cool and calm and doesn't flinch.
TREVOR
...youre gonna sell me out?! I should've killed you when I had the chance!
Trevor CHARGES at the Mechanic grabbing his collar, PUSHING him into the wall with one hand, pointing the GUN at his face with the other.
Fortuna CLOCKS Trevors temple with the back of her GUN. He FALLS over blacking out.
MECHANIC
Is he...is he dead?
FORTUNA
No.
MECHANIC
...for a second there I thought--
Fortuna AIMS her GUN back at him.
9.
FORTUNA
Stop...talking.
MECHANIC
I---
FORTUNA
(covering his mouth)
...do you hear that?
CHATTER can be heard in the HALLWAY. They've been found.
FORTUNA
Come with me.
He hesitates.
FORTUNA
Trust me you don't wanna stay here.
CUT TO:
Two MEN in black espionage style jumpsuits, carrying GUNS make their way down the HALLWAY. They stop by the ROOM speaking in RUSSIAN.
Moving in and scanning the space, one leans down checking Trevor's pulse. Another notices the curtains SWING back and forth over the OPEN BLACONY DOOR. He moves outside.
EXT. BALCONY DECK OVERLOOKING THE OCEAN - DAY
He steps on something. Leaning down he picks up a CARD.
Turning it, it's THE FOOL TAROT CARD.
The ROARING of a HELICOPTER approaches.
I AINT QUITE WHERE I THINK I AM picks back up towards the outro until the song ends.
The men watch above as Fortuna and the Mechanic escape.
BACK TO:
Baldwin pulls out a small PLASTIC BAG from his BRIEFCASE. Inside we see A CARD and a MATCHBOOK.
BALDWIN
(pulls out the tarot card)
Fortuna left a lot of these behind.
 
10.
cut TO:
EXT. Near CANNES, FRANCE - VILLA ON THE HILL - DAY
The HELICOPTER lands on a private estate. Exiting, the Mechanic walks behind Fortuna into a private Andalusian style COURTYARD.
Sensing his eyes on her.
FORTUNA
I wouldnt worry about contacting Mark. He probably thinks youre dead or captured by now.
She continues walking.
FORTUNA
..loose lips sunk ships. You shouldnt drink on the job.
The Mechanic stops in his tracks.
MECHANIC
...Who are you?
They now face each other.
MECHANIC
What do you want from me?
She eyes him up and down not responding.
MECHANIC
You're an American?...So Mark didn't send you.
FORTUNA
I told you I dont know who that is.
MECHANIC
What do you want with me?
She GESTURES for him to follow her.
CUT TO:
INT. GRAND HALL IN VILLA - DAY
FORTUNA
This way.
11.
The Mechanic follows her into the lavish style VILLA, an Andalusian rustic INTERIOR with vaulted ceilings, wooden floors, and century-old stone walls. A fusion of classic and modern.
Classical MUSIC plays around him as he takes in the marble floors, expensive dcor, paintings, and various antiques in the walls.
FORTUNA
(follows his gaze)
...its not mine if thats what youre thinking. I mean I do live here, but it's not mine.
SOMEONE ELSE (O.S.)
...right on time.
Behind the Mechanic stands a distinguished looking older MAN.
WORDS are typed on the bottom of the screen in courier typeface to the SOUND of a typewriter keys CLICKING:
"HENRI
A French man in his 60s. He looks put together and elegant in his navy-blue blazer over a white collared top. There is an air of wisdom, kindness, and class to this presence.
FORTUNA
(confidently)
...not a second late
HENRI
(eyeing the Mechanic)
New boyfriend?
FORTUNA
...Haven't decided yet.
She ignores the Mechanic's gaze. Henri slowly CIRCLES around him, sizing him.
HENRI
...hmm. And the necklace?
She unzips a GARTER around her thigh revealing the concealed NECKLACE. The GEM in the middle is half the size of a palm.
HENRI
(holding the necklace to the light)
Ah...magnifique.
12.
Henri SMASHES the GEM onto the table, SHATTERING it. The Mechanic watches Henri pull out a DEVICE from the shattered debris. A SMALL battery sized metal square. A code is ETCHED on the surface.
MECHANIC
Is that...a microprocessor?
FORTUNA
(suspiciously)
How do you know what that is?
MECHANIC
...I've work with circuit boards.
HENRI
This one is a little different...it's a military recording device.
MECHANIC
I'm sorry a what?
They continue speaking ignoring the confused man.
FORTUNA
We were followed. KGB agents...You were right. The Hand left it there for them. But if hes working with them, why steal it from him? Why cant he just...hand the recording over?
HENRI
(examining the object)
To make it look like a robbery. They get what they want, untraced...and he gets the insurance. Oldest trick in the book.
MECHANIC
When you say military what do you mean exactly?
She looks over The Mechanic.
FORTUNA
...What about him? MI6?
MECHANIC
What? Im...Im not
13.
FORTUNA
(ignoring him)
No...I doubt it. He was drunk on the job...and he mentioned his contact...Mark? Said his code name was The English.
HENRI
hmm...I know who that is.
MECHANIC
...hold on
HENRI
He really told you all that? Definitely not MI6.
FORTUNA
He wouldnt stop talking on the flight back.
MECHANIC
I...
FORTUNA
He talked about breaking into Operation Prometheus.
Henri looks stunned.
MECHANIC
(interrupts loudly)
HEY!
They turn to face him.
MECHANIC
Oh good! You do see me. What a-
HENRI
(still ignoring him)
No!...I know what youre thinking. No...are you mad?! It was a failed mission Fortuna!
FORTUNA
Henri. He...broke in.
Henri looks over the Mechanic.
HENRI
Tell me about Operation Prometheus.
14.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
So, I told them.
BACK TO:
BALDWIN
Well go on...
MECHANIC
You have my files.
BALDWIN
You got somewhere else to be?
He ashes the CIGARETTE in the empty CUP.
MECHANIC
At that point...Ive been working with Mark for a couple of years...
CUT TO:
INT. HEAD OFFICE - TRANQUILITY BASE HOTEL - NIGHT
We see the back of MARK hovering over a MODEL STRUCTURE of a casino. He is talking to his crew. We don't see Mark's face, just his figure in the shadows.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
He ran a small, six-man operation. Sometimes hed bring in a few extra hands but, he was pretty paranoid about outsiders. He thought everything was bugged.
BACK TO:
BALDWIN
(pulls out a file from his briefcase)
He wasnt wrong. We did listen.
cut to:
int. undisclosed location - night
A REEL TO REEL TAPE RECORDER spins rhythmically. TAPES are TURNED in compartments. STATIC chatter over RADIOS and CLICKING surround AGENTS in a small office. They hold RECIEVERS to their ears listening in on Mark.
15.
BALDWIN (V.O.)
It was mostly ramblings, conspiracy theories, moon landing hoax paranoia... And turns out The English liked to have lunch with the Reds every now and then...
back to:
BALDWIN
But I guess you know that by now. Go on.
MECHANIC
The jobs were small...banks, estates (pauses)...then he sent us to Monte Carlo.
Baldwin slides down a surveillance PHOTO of the CASINO on the table.
Baldwin (O.S.)
Casino de Monte-Carlo. Their security is so advanced you'd think they're a military operation.
cut TO:
EXT. CASINO DE MONTE CARLO - NIGHT
Marks CREW steps out of an unmarked VAN, dressed in all black. BALACLAVAS concealing their faces.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
It was six of us...All I had to do was break into the server room and rewire.
The crew SPLIT and the Mechanic is seen UNLOCKING the vents from the SERVER TOWER nearby.
BALDWIN (V.O.)
And what does that do?
The Mechanic is CRAWLING through the VENTS, breathing heavily, unarmed.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
Unlocks everything, all at once. No alarms, no power. That place was flooded with high society...so you can imagine.
(MORE)
16.
MECHANIC (V.O.) (CONT'D)
Every safe in every private room was like finding the Holy Grail...especially the casino vault.
He CLIMBS down into the SERVER ROOM and hunches over the wires. He begins to UNARM the surveillance program.
MECHANIC (V.O. CONT'D)
It's not often you see CCTV at work...their surveillance was unlike anything I've ever worked with.
He lifts his BALACLAVA.
BALDWIN (V.O.)
And you got in.
MECHANIC (V.O.)
I got in.
Wide eyed and smiling, he watches all the SCREENS on the surveillance wall BLACK OUT.
MECHANIC (V.O. CONT'D)
We got in....right into the lions den. None of us were prepared.
The Mechanic is startled by SOUNDS of distant GUNSHOTS and SCREAMS.
BACK TO:
BALDWIN
(slides more photos on the table)
And then you ran...and while you were crawling in vents, your crew were shot and killed by...oh how do you put it? (mockingly) high society?
The Mechanic looks down at the PHOTOS. A series of carnage.
BALDWIN
Your boss sent you right into the eye of the storm. You pissed off a lot of connected families. That place is a breeding ground for organized crime. He knew that too.
Baldwin notices his discomfort looking at the PHOTOS.
17.
BALDWIN
...so you told Henri and Fortuna
The Mechanic nods.
BALDWIN
...and?
MECHANIC
Henri insisted I join them for a drink.
cut TO:
INT. Henri's library - DAY
Scotch is being POURED.
Henri hovers over a CELLARETTE making a DRINK.
Fortuna sits with a DRINK in hand by the grand PIANO. The Mechanic stands in the door frame, alert.
HENRI
Please...come in. Have a seat.
The Mechanic takes in the lavish ROOM.
Classical MUSIC plays around him. His gaze follows the lined sculptures, antiques, and various paintings on the wall.
HENRI
Drink?
MECHANIC
...um...sure.
FORTUNA
Shocking.
HENRI
(smiling)
Play nice Fortuna.
Bewildered by the DCOR, the Mechanic lingers on a PAINTING on the wall.
HENRI
(handing him a drink)
Thats my favourite work...Giorgio De Chiricos
18.
MECHANIC
(finishing the sentence)
The Enigma of The Hour (he takes the drink)
Henri looks pleasantly surprised.
HENRI
A patron of the arts?
Not answering, the Mechanic turns to another PAINTING a few walls down. He looks like he's off in his own world thinking.
HENRI
Hmm...The Two Masks. Striking...isnt it?
The Mechanic is lost in the vision of the PAINTING. It's an image of two mask-like faces. One made of wood and the other a mannequin. Both faces seem to be STARING down at him.
HENRI
(staring at the painting)
The man without a voice, without eyes, and without a face. Some say hes a stage prop, a theater puppet, nothing more to it. Others say its two sides of a man...
MECHANIC
(keeping his eyes on the painting)
Twins...
HENRI
That too.
Eloquently, Henri begins to speak.
HENRI
...Take the Enigma of The Hour. There are three painted worlds on the canvas, or...three acts of a play if you like. The past, the present...the future. The past (He lifts his hand towards the painting) has a man standing in the sunlight. We can see the past perfectly. But the present and the future? He painted shadows around them, a world in limbo. It feels like a lost time. A world in the shadows. And the shadows?
(MORE)
19.
HENRI (CONT'D)
They hold many secrets, dont they?...yet they all exist at the same time on that canvas. All three worlds.
Henri paces towards the painting. The Mechanic follows with his gaze.
HENRI
And The Two Masks? Its two sides of the coin, two sides of one man. Him and his shadow self. And you know in folklore it's believed that one twin will always torment the other...almost like seeing all the faults you dislike of yourself in front of you, so you punish the image before you. But these twins occupy the same space and time...so who's the original and who's the copy? Who's right and who's wrong?
Henri turns his attention to the Mechanic.
HENRI
Chirico paints what he sees but he doesnt try to change the world around him. He doesnt try to change the image. No, no....he's doing something else in his work. He plants a thought from the image...
MECHANIC
...a thought?
HENRI
More of a question.
The Mechanic watches as Henri walks in closer towards him.
HENRI
...Whats real? And what isnt. Who's right and who's wrong? The answer is in the word...Enigma.
Fortuna looks as if she's heard this before. The Mechanic is holding onto his every word, almost in a trance.
HENRI
Your boss, Mark? I know him. Never worked with him, but I heard stories. He didnt tell you everything.
(MORE)
20.
HENRI (CONT'D)
He kept you in the shadows...just like those figures in the painting.
MECHANIC
...I came for the jewels. He didnt lie about that...
HENRI
...it was never about the jewels.
MECHANIC
(pauses)
...who are you people?
HENRI
Its not who I am, but what I can offer you.
Henri smiles
HENRI
How would you like to live out of the shadows?
The Mechanic pauses taking in his surroundings.
MECHANIC
Im guessing you didnt buy these.
Henri smiles.
MECHANIC
Right...well...this has been enlightening but I'm not staying.
HENRI
Hold on...
MECHANIC
No, I think we're done here.
He shoots down his drink.
MECHANIC
And theyre gonna be looking for me. So...(handing him the glass)...Sorry I can't stay for the rest of the art lesson.
FORTUNA
No one is coming for you, dont you get it?
BACK TO:
21.
Baldwin is seated. An open FOLDER in his hand.
BALDWIN
Your buddy Mark had a few friends in the Labour Party. Was inspired by Wilsons views on Vietnam. He even made a few friends in Red. But he didnt trust them either. Not the Reds, not the Brits...not even his own crew.
The Mechanic keeps his gaze on Baldwin. He doesn't flinch.
BALDWIN
(smiles knowing hes right)
We cant get Mark to talk yet, what with his paranoia parasite eating away at his brain. But your friend Trevor?...he told us Mark knew there was a tape...recordings outing his political friends, business partners for opposing the war...and their allegiance to the Reds. Even Trevor lied to you.
The Mechanic matches Baldwin's condescending stare.
BALDWIN
And Mark didnt tell you about that either it seems...He just knew youd obey...a foot soldier.
The Mechanic shifts in his seat trying to hide signs of agitation. Baldwin eggs him on.
BALDWIN
Trevor told us he had instructions from Mark. He was told to wait for you to crack the safe, hand over the jewels, and then...well...He was ordered to dispose of you.
cut TO:
MECHANIC
...no, Mark and I had a deal.
HENRI
Men like him, theyre...idealists. He would sacrifice his own for a cause. For a mission.
 
22.
BACK TO:
BALDWIN
And in this case? He knew you could break into anything, untraced, getting him what he wanted.
Baldwin scoffs.
BALDWIN
And he didnt want those recordings to protect his friends either.
cut to:
INT. TRANQUILITY BASE HOTEL - NIGHT
We see the back of Mark. He sits facing wall to wall TELEVISION SCREENS. FOOTAGE of GUESTS in their private rooms, at the bar, in the pool. The surveillance looks more advanced for its time.
BALDWIN (V.O.)
We went through his surveillance and security units. He was tapped into everyone...for months. He had information on every elite guest that ever stepped foot in that hotel. Politicians, bankers, investors, off shore accounts. Those recordings meant nothing to him in the long run. He wanted ownership, control. He's a...
cut TO:
HENRI
...a mad man. You said he called your heist Prometheus?
MECHANIC
(confused)
...yes(pausing)...he said something about me climbing the tower to black out the world. I can work my way around in the dark.
back to:
BALDWIN
(mockingly)
Like you're Batman? Jesus..(scoffs)...go on.
23.
The Mechanic continues.
cut to:
HENRI
Hmm....Like Prometheus climbing the mountain to steal fire from the Gods.
Henri gets closer.
HENRI
In the myth, Prometheus is caught and tortured for his sin...Mark was telling you from the start how it would end for you.

FORTUNA
And the KGB (turns to the Mechanic) if Trevor failed to kill you, they would have finished the job. You were set up either way.
MECHANIC
(talking to himself)
Bastard...

MECHANIC
(still talking to himself)
This was it. This was my last job...
FORTUNA
Meaning what?

MECHANIC

HENRI
I agree.

HENRI
Thats all in the past. Im only interested in the future.
24.
MECHANIC
Well...Good luck with yours. Mine is off this island. I didn't sign up for this.

HENRI (O.S.)
You can't walk off the island.

HENRI

HENRI

Henri interrupts.
HENRI
...I can help you start over.

HeNRI
Ah...That's what you want isn't it? A new slate? That's what you told Mark? And I'm guessing a man like him has a hard time letting go...

HENRI
If he finds out you're alive, he'll come for you.
MECHANIC
Why do you care?
FORTUNA
We don't.
HENRI
Tut tut tut, Fortuna.

25.
HENRI
I asked you if you'd like to live out of the shadows. I can give you a new slate, make you a free man...retired spy if you may.

HENRI
You told Fortuna you broke in. Can you do it again?
MECHANIC
You...want me to work for you??
HENRI
